 MZANSI has recorded 194 more Covid-19 deaths, taking the
number of deaths to 50 271. Health Minister Zweli Mkhize said the Covid-19 deaths were
reported in the following provinces: Eastern Cape 8, Free State 29, Gauteng 43,
KwaZulu Natal 80, Limpopo 15, Northern Cape 7, and the Western Cape 12 bringing
the total number of deaths to 50271. A total of 23 753 tests were conducted in the past 24 hours,
with 856 new cases, which represents a 4% positivity rate, the recoveries now
stand at 1 433 320, representing a recovery rate of 94,6%. #COVID19 UPDATE: A total of 23 753 tests were conducted in the last 24 hrs, with 856 new cases, which represents a 4%... 